# Foldline Environment Variables Template
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values
# NEVER commit .env to version control

# ============================================================
# Lemon Squeezy Payment Integration
# ============================================================
# Used by the marketing website (SvelteKit) to generate checkout URLs

# Your Lemon Squeezy Store ID
# Find this in: Dashboard → Settings → Store
# Used for: API calls to create checkout sessions (optional, advanced usage)
LEMONSQUEEZY_STORE_ID=your_store_id_here

# Your Lemon Squeezy Product ID or Variant ID
# Find this in: Dashboard → Products → [Your Product] → Variants
# Used for: Constructing checkout URLs
LEMONSQUEEZY_PRODUCT_ID=your_product_variant_id_here

# Your Lemon Squeezy API Key (read/write access)
# Find this in: Dashboard → Settings → API
# Used for: Creating checkout sessions dynamically (optional)
#           Validating license keys (future enhancement)
# ⚠️  KEEP THIS SECRET - Never expose in client-side code
LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# Direct Checkout URL (Simple Approach - Recommended for MVP)
# This is the full hosted checkout URL from Lemon Squeezy
# Find this in: Dashboard → Products → [Your Product] → Copy Checkout URL
# Used for: Simple "Buy Now" button that redirects to Lemon Squeezy
# Example: https://foldline.lemonsqueezy.com/checkout/buy/XXXXXXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXX-XXXXXXXXXXXX
LEMONSQUEEZY_CHECKOUT_URL=https://foldline.lemonsqueezy.com/checkout/buy/YOUR_CHECKOUT_ID

# Webhook Secret (Optional - Future Enhancement)
# Find this in: Dashboard → Settings → Webhooks → [Your Webhook] → Secret
# Used for: Verifying webhook signatures from Lemon Squeezy
#           Tracking purchases in real-time
#           Automating license key delivery (if not using Lemon Squeezy's built-in email)
# ⚠️  KEEP THIS SECRET
# LEMONSQUEEZY_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret_here

# ============================================================
# Implementation Notes
# ============================================================

# MARKETING WEBSITE (SvelteKit):
# - Reads LEMONSQUEEZY_CHECKOUT_URL to power the "Buy Foldline" button
# - Optionally uses LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY to create dynamic checkout sessions
#   (e.g., for pay-what-you-want with user-selected amounts)
# - Never exposes API keys in client-side JavaScript

# DESKTOP APP (Tauri):
# - Does NOT need any Lemon Squeezy credentials
# - Users provide their own license keys received via email
# - License keys are stored locally using Tauri secure storage

# DONATION CALCULATOR (tools/donations):
# - Optionally uses LEMONSQUEEZY_API_KEY to fetch transaction data
# - Can work offline with CSV exports (no API key required)

# ============================================================
# Security Reminders
# ============================================================

# ✅ DO:
# - Copy this file to .env and add real values
# - Add .env to .gitignore (already done)
# - Use server-side only for API keys (never in frontend)
# - Rotate API keys if exposed

# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit .env with real values
# - Expose API keys in client-side code
# - Share API keys in screenshots or logs
# - Use production keys in development (use Lemon Squeezy test mode)

# ============================================================
# Testing with Lemon Squeezy Test Mode
# ============================================================

# Lemon Squeezy supports test mode for development:
# 1. Enable test mode in Dashboard → Settings
# 2. Create test products and variants
# 3. Use test API keys (prefix: lssk_test_...)
# 4. Generate test checkout URLs
# 5. Use test credit cards (e.g., 4242 4242 4242 4242)

# When ready for production:
# 1. Switch to live mode in Lemon Squeezy
# 2. Update .env with live credentials
# 3. Test thoroughly before launch

